<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="451" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,150,285]" pageId="21" pageNumber="451">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,222,248]" pageId="21" pageNumber="451">Comments.</emphasis>
This species is known as the green-bellied bug. Both adults and nymphs cause damage to the base of the plants, through the leaf sheath, reaching the inner leaves. Fifth instar nymphs are green.
</paragraph>
